#FY16 FY17 targets: 5-7% FFO per security growth & 25.5c distribution per security, assuming no material change in market conditions

#FY16 Stockland is broadening and deepening market reach to improve community creation capabilities and appeal to wider variety of customers
#FY16 Operating profit in Retirement Living was up 19.7% on FY15, reflecting strong sales, active management and improved efficiency
#FY16 Our Residential business continues to focus on affordability and community creation. More than 75% of buyers are owner occupiers
#FY16 Our Residential portfolio settled record 6,135 lots & achieved significant operating profit growth of 38.8% in FY16
#FY16 Comparable Office FFO increased 9.9%, reflecting good leasing momentum and strength of Sydney market where bulk of assets located
#FY16 Logistics and Business Parks portfolio delivered good profit growth with comparable FFO up 3.7%, reflecting positive leasing momentum
#FY16 Our Retail portfolio recorded 3.7% growth in comparable FFO and continued sales growth
#FY16 Maintained strong balance sheet & A-/stable credit rating, supporting investment in future of business
#FY16 Strong results from disciplined strategy execution: growing asset returns & customer base, operational excellence, capital strength
#FY16 Delivered target distribution per security of 24.5 cents in FY16, representing payout ratio of 88% of underlying EPS and 79% of FFO
#FY16 Solid underlying EPS growth of 7.3% and FFO per security growth of 11.1% in FY16
#FY16 Funds from operations up 12.5% on FY15, with significant contributions across Residential, Commercial Property, Retirement Living
